# Data Models for CoinAtlasApp

## Core Models

### Trading Pair
```dart
class TradingPair {
  final String id;           // e.g., "EUR/USD"
  final double buyRate;
  final double sellRate;
  final double changePercent;
  final String trend;        // "up" or "down"
  final String summary;      // Brief news/event affecting this pair
  final List<double> chartData;
}
```

### Sentiment
```dart
class Sentiment {
  final String asset;        // e.g., "Bitcoin"
  final String mood;         // e.g., "Optimistic", "Cautious"
  final String trendDirection; // e.g., "Increasing", "Stable"
  final List<double> chartData;
  final String summary;      // Brief explanation of sentiment
}
```

### News Event
```dart
class NewsEvent {
  final String title;
  final String timeAgo;      // e.g., "2 hours ago"
  final String summary;
  final String impact;       // e.g., "High", "Medium", "Low"
  final List<String> affectedPairs; // Trading pairs affected by this news
}
```

### Settings Item
```dart
class SettingsItem {
  final String title;
  final String icon;
  final String route;        // Navigation route
  final Color iconColor;
}
```

## Data Flow Guidelines

- Models should be immutable (all fields are final)
- No complex inheritance hierarchies
- Keep models focused on data representation only
- Use factory constructors for creating models from JSON
- Include toJson() methods for serialization
